 que reflejan cómo en Neuman la identidad no preexiste, sino que es narrativizada, y que, por tanto, evoluciona a lo largo de su obra.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2022z9783110767148oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396869265440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783968692654423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783968692654/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022